
[TestProjectCmd_ShowsHelp - 1]
Manage the GitOps project files (the on-disk project structure) without contacting a live cluster. These commands scaffold and transform the project — e.g. initializing a new project and managing its cluster environments — as opposed to the cluster commands that operate on a running cluster.

Usage:
  project [flags]
  project [command]

Available Commands:
  completion        Generate the autocompletion script for the specified shell
  env               Manage the cluster environments declared in the workspace
  help              Help about any command
  init              Initialize a new project

Flags:
  -h, --help   help for project

Use "project [command] --help" for more information about a command.

---
